# Normalize line endings so a contributor's core.autocrlf can't change what ships.
* text=auto eol=lf

# The provenance hook is embedded verbatim into the binary via include_str! and then
# written to git's hooks dir. It runs under the POSIX sh git-for-windows bundles,
# which aborts on a trailing CR — so it MUST stay LF-only regardless of platform.
# (A build test asserts `!HOOK_BODY.contains('\r')`; this keeps the checkout honest.)
hooks/prepare-commit-msg text eol=lf
*.sh text eol=lf
